// =============================================================================
// DESIGN NOTES
// =============================================================================
//
// 1. Single organization
//    Pilot seeds one row: slug = "rupee-catalyst", name = "Rupee Catalyst".
//    organizationId required on all ECM rows for future multi-tenant without redesign.
//
// 2. Timestamps
//    Domain types use createdOn/modifiedOn (ISO strings). Repository maps ↔ createdAt/updatedAt.
//    lastActiveOn ↔ lastActiveAt.
//
// 3. Mobile uniqueness
//    @@unique([organizationId, mobilePrimary]) — includes progressive pending-* placeholders.
//    Service layer generates unique pending mobile values per create.
//
// 4. Company name uniqueness
//    Case-insensitive: migration index ecm_companies_org_name_ci_key on lower(company_name)
//    WHERE enabled = true. Service layer findEcmCompanyByName aligns with this.
//
// 5. Soft archive
//    Contacts: status = archived + enabled = false
//    Companies: status = archived + enabled = false
//    No hard DELETE in Phase 1B.
//
// 6. JSONB fields
//    roleProfiles, relationship meta — flexible MIR without column explosion.
//
// 7. Non-destructive migration
//    All new tables. Existing users / refresh_tokens / password_reset_tokens untouched.
//
// 8. Directory Registry filters (UI — separate domain entities)
//    All · Individuals · Companies · Business Roles
//    Individual row → Contact Workspace · Company row → Company Workspace
//
// 9. Supabase Storage
//    Not in this migration. Document tables arrive CO-SPRINT-121.
//
// 10. EOLE
//     Not in this migration. Phase 2A only for Pilot.
//
// =============================================================================
